cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CC

This paper deals with the computational complexity of fair allocation mechanisms, specifically in the context of competitive equilibrium with equal incomes (CEEI). This topic falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for finding the A-CEEI allocation, as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques for approximating the equilibrium.
